<br>
The discussion is still going on as to what the real %'s are.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://seq.sourceforge.net/showthread.php?s=f929e2522b958129658247d459b4394d&amp;threadid=1878">seq.sourceforge.net/showthread.php?s=f929e2522b958129658247d459b4394d&amp;threadid=1878</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
In short, lvl 60 will now take 50% longer to go from no XP in the bar to full XP(this accounts for the 75% modifier) and starting at lvl 55 mobs jump up in reward considerably. Lvl 54 and below mobs really aren't very attractive although there has been no change to them in particular, its only that level 60 is now longer which makes lvl 54 and lower mobs seem to give less XP.<br>
<br>
I believe we should get a CON system to reflect this variation.<br>
<br>
How this applies (or even whether it applies) to AAXP is not known at this point. It seems that the bonus for mobs lvl 55+ would still be in effect but whether you recieve 75% less per kill (on all kills while lvl 60) because lvl 60 is longer is neither proven/disproven yet. They are waiting on more data. <br>
<br>
There are two possibilities for gaining AAXP at lvl 60:<br>
<br>
1. The AAXP gained for mobs lvl 54 and below has not changed. For a level 55 mob you are receiving 95% more than before. A level 56 mob gives 108% more. More data at this time has not been gathered for level 57+ mobs but it likely increases even more.<br>
<br>
2. You are receiving the XP as stated in option one but multiplied by 0.75. This would mean level 54 and lower give 25% less XP than before. Level 55 mobs give 46.25% more. Level 56 mobs give 56% more than before.<br>
<br>
My feeling is that option one will be found to be correct, which is the best news we could get. No hard data yet on AAXP to prove/disprove this yet though. <p><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=157667">Junu Peeth</a></b> on Mithaniel Marr<br>
Human Monk in his 57th year</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueyston.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eyston</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/10/02 1:07:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=309.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hard Data on Exp change</span><hr size=1> The dealio.  Everything level 54 and below is normal.  Everything 55 and above is superfied.<br>
